general_exclusion_criteria:
history of splenectomy (may be reconsidered by principal investigator);
allergic reaction attributable to ruxolitinib or its formulation constituents;
requirement for strong CYP3A4 inhibitory medications;
use of any other investigational agents;
uncontrolled intercurrent illnesses;
laboratory evidence of insufficient hepatic function (bilirubin or transaminase levels exceed stipulated limits);
insufficient renal function (creatinine clearance below mandated level);
psychiatric or psychosocial circumstances compromising adherence;
pregnancy or breastfeeding;
failure to commit to adequate contraception measures for individuals of reproductive potential.

