History of persisting (>Grade 1) toxicity attributable to prior therapy (excluding mild alopecia or peripheral neuropathy ≤Grade 2);
solid organ transplantation;
concurrent enrolment in another investigational therapeutic trial;
leptomeningeal disease;
untreated or symptomatic central nervous system metastasis (treated brain metastases allowed if stable ≥4 weeks);
active autoimmune disorders—including inflammatory bowel disease, rheumatoid arthritis, scleroderma, systemic lupus erythematosus, vasculitis, Guillain‑Barre syndrome, Myasthenia Gravis—and other autoimmune conditions requiring systemic immunosuppression;
significant cardiovascular disease (stroke or myocardial infarction <6 months ago, unstable angina, congestive heart failure NYHA Class II‑IV, uncontrolled arrhythmias);
uncontrolled intercurrent serious infection or psychiatric disorder limiting adherence;
other active malignancies requiring treatment or a history of another malignancy within 2 years (except adequately treated non‑melanoma skin cancer, superficial bladder tumors, localized prostate intraepithelial neoplasia, cervical carcinoma in situ, or other indolent disease disease‑free >1 year);
use of systemic glucocorticoids ≥10 mg/day prednisone-equivalent within 2 weeks before registration (unless for non‑autoimmune indication);
pregnancy or lactation, and lack of reliable contraceptive measures for persons of reproductive potential;
known human immunodeficiency virus infection;
active hepatitis B or C viral infection (surface antigen positive or detectable viral nucleic acid);
severe hypersensitivity reaction to study‑related products or structurally similar substances;
receipt of a live attenuated vaccine within 2 weeks preceding enrollment;
history of grade 2 or greater hemolytic anemia of any etiology.

