history of grade 2 or greater hemolytic anemia of any etiology.

History of persistent (> Grade 1) toxicities from prior anticancer therapies (except alopecia);
Recent palliative radiotherapy within 14 days or definitive radiotherapy within 42 days of Cycle 1 Day 1;
Receipt of any other investigational agents;
Allergic reaction to peposertib, liposomal doxorubicin, or chemically similar substances;
Inability to discontinue strong CYP3A4/5, CYP2C9, or CYP2C19 modulators or substrates with narrow therapeutic indexes as stipulated;
Inability to discontinue proton‑pump inhibitors appropriately;
Left ventricular ejection fraction below institution’s lower limits of normal;
Uncontrolled intercurrent illnesses;
Incapacity to swallow oral tablet formulations;
Active or progressing brain metastases or leptomeningeal disease when immediate CNS-directed therapy is anticipated;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Previous treatment with a DNA‑protein kinase (PK) inhibitor.

