Severe cardiac comorbidity (congestive heart failure or cardiomyopathy with EF ≤50%);
Severe pulmonary comorbidity (DLCO ≤65% or FEV1 ≤65%, resting dyspnoea, or oxygen dependence);
ECOG performance status greater than 3 (except discussed cases);
Abnormal laboratory parameters indicating impaired kidney, pancreas, or liver function outside specified limits;
Corrected QT interval >480 ms;
Recent major surgery (<2 weeks);
Uncontrolled infection;
Unstable cardiovascular conditions (symptomatic CHF NYHA III–IV, unstable angina, significant arrhythmia, MI or stroke within 90 days);
History of pulmonary arterial hypertension;
Significant pleural effusion causing respiratory compromise;
Alcohol abuse needing medical treatment;
Active or unresolved hepatitis B/C infection;
Known HIV infection;
Serious non‑cancer bleeding disorders;
Concurrent malignant disease requiring systemic therapy;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Inability to tolerate oral medication administration.

