History of recurrent head and neck cancer, parotid gland cancer, or second primary cancer (other than treated basal cell or cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma of the skin or in‑situ cervical carcinoma);
Systemic autoimmune diseases involving the salivary glands (e.g., Sjögren’s syndrome);
Active viral infections including Epstein‑Barr virus (unless resolved), hepatitis C virus, and HIV;
Diagnosis of myasthenia gravis;
Personal or familial predisposition to acute/chronic angle‑closure glaucoma;
Known allergy or hypersensitivity to glycopyrrolate;
Current cigarette smoking or nicotine vape product use within the last 3 years;
Alcohol misuse or heavy drinking exceeding guideline limits within the last 3 years;
Poorly controlled diabetes mellitus (Hemoglobin A1c >7%)).

Active or progressing central nervous system metastases or leptomeningeal disease (unless meet stability criteria outlined above);
Persistent Grade > 1 toxicities from earlier systemic anticancer regimens (aside from alopecia and vitiligo);
Concomitant systemic corticosteroids dosing higher than 10 mg/day prednisone equivalents;
Uncontrolled intercurrent illness such as serious cardiac, pulmonary, hepatic, or renal disorders;
Known human immunodeficiency virus infection or active hepatitis B or C infection;
Pregnancy or lactation.

Active or history of pneumonitis/interstitial lung disease, pulmonary fibrosis requiring systemic steroids, or imaging findings suggesting ILD/pneumonitis;
Immunodeficiency or active autoimmune disease needing chronic systemic corticosteroids (>10 mg/day prednisolone-equivalent) or other immunosuppression within the preceding 2 years;
Sensory peripheral neuropathy grade ≥ 2 (applies to Part 2);
Clinically significant untreated gastrointestinal disorders (e.g., inflammatory bowel disease, severe ulcers, ongoing GI bleed, chronic diarrhoea);
Recent major hemorrhage (hematemesis, massive hemoptysis, melena) within 6 months;
Major surgical procedure or radiation therapy completed ≤4 weeks before enrollment or radiation involving >30 % bone marrow;
Known hypersensitivity to PF‑07985045 or any co-administered investigational/comparator drug components;
Significant hematologic toxicity,
Renal insufficiency,
Hepatic dysfunction.

