Has untreated central nervous system metastases;
has a glioma or other primary CNS malignant neoplasm;
has spinal cord compression or symptomatic/uncontrolled epidural disease;
history of intracranial or spinal cord haemorrhage;
active neurological paraneoplastic syndromes;
uncontrolled pleural, pericardial effusions or ascites needing frequent drainage;
current or past autoimmune diseases or immune deficiencies (e.g., Myasthenia Gravis, Systemic Lupus Erythematosus, Rheumatoid Arthritis, Inflammatory Bowel Disease, vasculitides);
use of systemic immunosuppressants exceeding prednisone >10 mg/day (or equivalents) within two weeks before starting study drugs;
significant recent cardiovascular events (myocardial infarction, NYHA Class III–IV heart failure, unstable arrhythmias) within six months;
recent arterial thrombotic event (stroke/TIA) within six months;
active hepatitis A/B/C infections (unless virologically suppressed);
untreated/HIV infection (well controlled HIV permissible);
previous allogenic hematopoietic stem cell transplantation or solid‑organ transplantation;
treatment with systemic immunostimulatory agents (interferon, IL‑2) within four weeks;
severe hypersensitivity to monoclonal antibodies or related biologics;
past or current interstitial lung disease/pneumonitis or radiographic signs of active pneumonitis;
participation in another investigational drug study within three weeks (or five drug half‑lives) of dosing.

