History of severe allergic reaction to study drugs;
Active uncontrolled infection (bacterial, viral, fungal, or parasitic) requiring intravenous therapy;
Positive blood culture within 48 hours of enrollment;
Recent fever (>38.2°C) with infectious source and untreated bacteremia;
Ongoing steroid therapy for disease control without a stable/decreasing dose for ≥7 days;
Concurrent use of other investigational anticancer agents;
Use of additional antitumour agents, radiation therapy, or immunotherapy aside from stipulated wash‑outs;
Receipt of anti‑GVHD or organ‑rejectant medication within 4 weeks;
Significant cardiac impairment (heart failure NYHA class III/IV);
Severe hepatic insufficiency (bilirubin >1.5 times ULN or transaminases >3 times ULN);
Renal dysfunction (creatinine clearance <70 ml/min/1.73 m²);
Pulmonary limitation (oxygen saturation ≤94% on ambient air);
Uncontrolled central nervous system hemorrhage or mass effect;
Known DNA repair disorders (Fanconi anaemia, Bloom syndrome, etc.);
Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Inability to comply with study procedures owing to psychosocial or cognitive issues.

